      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and fluid property inputs traceable to calibrated measurements or published reference values; sensitivity to key inputs documented.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog viscosity measured with cone-and-plate rheometer (±2%). Pump geometry digitized from CMM measurements of physical impeller (±10 µm). Sensitivity analysis on viscosity (±10%) shows RHI variation of ±3.1%, within acceptable bounds. Dataset fda-gcbp-hemolysis-validation-set-2025 provides the reference fluid property and operating-condition inputs used to parameterize the model; the dataset was collected and frozen prior to the most recent model revision (see dataVintage). The responsible engineer noted in the model change log that revision v3r2 corrected a minor impeller tip-clearance gap from 0.18 mm to 0.21 mm to match updated CMM data, and assessed this change as not material to the fluid property inputs drawn from the dataset. No formal re-validation against the updated geometry was performed, as the team judged the dataset's boundary conditions to remain applicable without re-collection."
    },
